<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="610" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 103.97/163: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-12">January 12,
                                1919</date>.<lb/>[Received January 13—12:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>68. For Hoover.</p>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Only yesterday I have been informed of the European Relief
                            Administration. I have delegated by wire Attolico to represent Italian
                            Government at the first meeting. I shall ask President Orlando on his
                            return to appoint the two permanent Italian delegates. I expect the new
                            body will deal with matters included in your telegram of the 7th in
                            regard Roumania. Crespi.”</p>
                    </quote>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>